        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1927"/>, p. <citedRange>157</citedRange></bibl> (mention of find);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XI.41</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>095800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65856"><name nymRef="#Ὑπέρβιος"><supplied reason="lost">Ὑ</supplied><unclear>π</unclear>έρβιος</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62685"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀκέσανδρος">Ἀκεσάνδρω</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλωνι</name></persName> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Hyperbios fils d'Akésandros <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> à Apollon comme dîme.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Hyperbios son of Akesandros <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> to Apollo as a tithe.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Hyperbios figlio di Akesandros <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> ad Apollo come decima.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ὑπέρβιος</foreign> is only attested for this man in Cyrenaica. There are a few occurrences elsewhere with no 
                special localisation.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
